{"word":"ὠρέω","slug":"ὠρέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n116323\" key=\"w)re/w\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">ὠρέω</orth>, in <tns opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tns\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ pres.\">pres.</a></tns> <mood opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"mood\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ part.\">part.</a></mood> <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὠρεόντων· φροντιζόντων,</foreign> <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Hp.\">Hp.</a></author> </bibl> ap. <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Gal.\">Gal.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">19.157</biblScope> </bibl>: but <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὡρέοντα· χρονίζοντα, ὧρος γὰρ ὁ χρόνος καὶ ὡρογράφοι οἱ περὶ χρόνου γράψαντες,</foreign> <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Hp.\">Hp.</a></author> </bibl> ap. <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Erot.</author> </bibl>: but the latter word may be imaginary, the reference being perh. to <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὡραῖα ἐόντα</foreign> in <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Id.\">Id.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Loc.Hom.\">Loc.Hom.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">38</biblScope> </bibl>; neither has been found in our codd. of <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Hp.\">Hp.</a></author> </bibl>:—we have also <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὠρήσαντα· φυλάσσοντα,</foreign> and <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὠρήσσονται· φυλάσσονται,</foreign> <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Hsch.\">Hsch.</a></author> </bibl>; <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὠρεῖν· φυλάττειν, ὅθεν καὶ ὁ θυρωρὸς λέγεται,</foreign> Id., which together with <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg4099.tlg001:686:54\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ EM\">EM</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">686.54</biblScope></bibl>, al., <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0654.tlg002:1\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Corn.</author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\">ND</title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1</biblScope></bibl>, suggests that <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὠρέω</foreign> is coined by Grammarians to expl. words in <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">-ωρός.</foreign> </entryFree>"}]}